		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">CKY-2K/Clay Man wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What waveforms does it use?</div><br />FDS audio is a programmable waveform, like a higher-quality version of the Game Boy version of the triangle channel. I'll guess that some of the "analog" perception comes from hardware vibrato.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Did FDS games were not able to use DMC?</div>
<br />FDS games could use all six channels at the same time: square 1, square 2, triangle, noise, DMC, and FDS audio.

		

