		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, the FDS channel is a waveform channel like the Gameboy's channel 3, or any of the TG-16's channels - if it seems smoother, it's likely because it has both a higher sample resolution and a longer waveform buffer than the Gameboy (64 6-bit samples versus 16 4-bit samples) - this would allow for, say, a nice smooth sine curve. It also has a frequency modulation waveform (32 3-bit signed samples,) volume control, and an envelope generator, none of which Gameboy channel 3 had. It's just a pity so few games made use of it, even games that originated on FDS.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


